Real Madrid on Friday confirmed that its winger, Takefusa Kubo, has left the club to join Getafe on loan. Kubo, 19, will now remain at Getafe until the end of the 2020/21 season. Real Madrid made the announcement in a statement ahead of their away La Liga clash with Osasuna on Saturday night. The statement read: “Real Madrid CF and Getafe CF have agreed to loan player Takefusa Kubo until the end of this season.” Kubo joined Real Madrid in the summer of 2019. The Japanese star was loaned out to Mallorca and Villarreal by Zinedine Zidane’s side in the past. He made his full Japan international debut on the 9th of June, 2019 against El Salvador.